Sentencas: In this work, a framework of charge transports in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs) with considering current leakage is developed by assuming four electrode reactions.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage

Sentencas: Current leakage occurs when electron holes pass through the electrolyte and combine with electrons at the anode side.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage

Sentencas: An analytical solution of leakage currents is proposed depending on the Nernst-Planck equation.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage

Sentencas: On the basis of the analysis expression, a mathematical model of H-SOFCs is proposed, which can provide the information about current-voltage characteristics, leakage current density, Faraday and energy efficiencies.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage

Sentencas: Furthermore, H-SOFCs with the BaZr0.8Y0.2O3 electrolyte are fabricated and tested, and the proposed model well reproduces the experimental data.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage

Sentencas: The simulation results indicate that current leakage primarily affects the H-SOFC performance when the output voltage is close to the OCV.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage

Sentencas: Both Faraday efficiencies and energy efficiencies decrease with increasing operating temperatures due to the existence of current leakage.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with current leakage
